# ─── ML artifacts ───
# Trained models are gitignored by default. EXCEPTION (decision 2026-05-28): the one
# committed HelpNeed artifact is checked in so the deployed turn loop loads it at boot
# with no network fetch — it is ~280 KB (size set by tree count/depth, not row count),
# and its provenance lives in the commit message + README (the 1.44 GB training data
# is gitignored, so the binary's source can't show in a diff). S3/model-registry
# hosting is the upgrade path if the model grows or needs independent versioning
# (CLAUDE.md §8.6 — premature at this size). Reproduce: app.helpneed.train_pipeline
# with WHOLLYMATH_EDMCUP_ROW_LIMIT=5000000 + WHOLLYMATH_HELPNEED_OUT (RESEARCH.md §7.2).
*.joblib
*.pkl
!backend/app/helpneed/artifacts/helpneed_v1.joblib

# ─── Local training-data pulls (ASSISTments / DataShop traces) ───
# Large, license-bound interaction logs; never committed (live in S3 for prod).
backend/data/

# ─── V2 AI-expansion upgrade-path tracker (local-only, same posture as TODO.md) ───
V2_TODO.md

# ─── Pre-rendered TTS audio bank (build artifact; Slice A — backend/app/tts/) ───
# The cached Hope audio + manifest the avatar lip-syncs to is BUILD OUTPUT, regenerated by
# app.tts.render_bank from the finite spoken-string bank. Audio binaries don't belong in git
# (V2_TODO 2.1); served as static assets off CloudFront in prod. Never commit the .mp3s.
backend/app/tts/cache/

# ─── Lesson-world background images (frontend/public) ───
# Large pre-toned storybook backdrops a lesson wears (the tutor-bg pool) + the lesson fallback.
# Kept out of git as binary assets; they live on disk and `vite build` copies public/ into dist/,
# so the LOCAL build (and the CDK deploy, which ships frontend/dist) still includes them. NOTE: a
# FRESH CLONE / CI build will have no lesson backdrops until these are restored. The pool in
# Tutor.tsx (TUTOR_BACKGROUNDS) must name only files present on disk.
frontend/public/tutor-bg-*.jpg
frontend/public/lesson-world-bg.jpeg
